            {# How to use #}
            <article class="card p-2">
                <div class="card-header">
                    <h2>üß© How to use</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <p class="p-1">
                        Add <code class="text-bold text-primary">data-js="collapse"</code> to the button and set
                        <code class="text-bold text-primary">data-target</code> to the ID of the matching
                        <code class="text-bold text-primary">.accordion-body</code>. The script toggles the panel and
                        updates
                        <code class="text-bold text-primary">aria-expanded</code> automatically.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </article>

            {# Sizes #}
            <article class="card p-2">
                <div class="card-header">
                    <h2>üìè Sizes</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    These classes apply only to the accordion buttons.
                    Each one already includes both the style and the size, so just pick the one you need.
                    <div class="row mt-2">
                        <div class="col-12 col-4-xs">
                            <div class="card p-2">
                                <code class="text-bold text-primary">.accordion-btn</code>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-12 col-4-xs">
                            <div class="card p-2">
                                <code class="text-bold text-primary">.accordion-btn-sm</code>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-12 col-4-xs">
                            <div class="card p-2">
                                <code class="text-bold text-primary">.accordion-btn-md</code>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-12 col-4-xs">
                            <div class="card p-2">
                                <code class="text-bold text-primary">.accordion-btn-lg</code>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </article>

            {# Colors #}
            <article class="card p-2">
                <div class="card-header">
                    <h2>üé® Colors</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    Button colors and accordion borders are handled separately.
                    Apply these classes directly on the element you want to style.

                    <div class="row mt-2">
                        <div class="col-12 col-4-xs">
                            <div class="card p-2">
                                <code class="text-bold text-primary">btn-{color}</code>
                                <br><small>Apply on the button <br>(with hover)</small>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-12 col-4-xs">
                            <div class="card p-2">
                                <code class="text-bold text-primary">bg-{color}</code>
                                <br><small>Apply on the button <br>(no hover)</small>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-12 col-4-xs">
                            <div class="card p-2">
                                <code class="text-bold text-primary">accordion-{color}</code>
                                <br><small>Apply on the <code>.accordion</code> container <br>(borders only)</small>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </article>

            {# Accessibility #}
            <article class="card p-2">
                <div class="card-header">
                    <h2>üìå Accessibility</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <p class="p-1">
                        For accessibility, set <code class="text-bold text-primary">aria-expanded</code> in your HTML
                        only once to match the
                        initial state. After that, the script updates its value automatically.
                    </p>

                    <p class="p-1">
                        Add <code class="text-bold text-primary">aria-controls</code> to link the button to the panel
                        ID.
                        This helps screen readers understand which content is being toggled.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </article>

            {# State #}
            <article class="card p-2">
                <div class="card-header">
                    <h2>üìå State</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <p class="p-1">
                        To keep a panel open on page load, add the <code class="text-bold text-primary">.show</code>
                        class on the
                        <code class="text-bold text-primary">.accordion-body</code>.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </article>

            {# Spacing rules #}
            <article class="card p-2">
                <div class="card-header">
                    <h2>üìå Spacing rules</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <p class="p-1">
                        Do not add <code class="text-bold text-primary">padding</code> or <code
                            class="text-bold text-primary">margin</code> on
                        <code class="text-bold text-primary">.accordion-body</code>. They are always forced to <code
                            class="text-bold text-primary">0</code>.
                        Add spacing on elements inside the panel (like <code class="text-bold text-primary">p</code> or
                        <code class="text-bold text-primary">ul</code>),
                        not on <code class="text-bold text-primary">.accordion-body</code>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </article>

            {# Varibles #}
            <article class="card p-2">
                <div class="card-header">
                    <h2>‚öôÔ∏è Variables CSS</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <div class="table-responsive">
                        <table class="table">
                            <thead>
                            <tr class="text-left">
                                <th>Class</th>
                                <th>Description</th>
                            </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>

                            <tr>
                                <td><code class="text-bold text-primary">--accordion-bg-color</code></td>
                                <td>Background color of the accordion.</td>
                            </tr>

                            <tr>
                                <td><code class="text-bold text-primary">--accordion-border-color</code></td>
                                <td>Color of the borders.</td>
                            </tr>

                            <tr>
                                <td><code class="text-bold text-primary">--accordion-border-radius</code></td>
                                <td>Corner radius.</td>
                            </tr>

                            <tr>
                                <td><code class="text-bold text-primary">--accordion-border-style</code></td>
                                <td>Border style (solid, dashed, etc.).</td>
                            </tr>

                            <tr>
                                <td><code class="text-bold text-primary">--accordion-border-width</code></td>
                                <td>Border thickness.</td>
                            </tr>

                            <tr>
                                <td><code class="text-bold text-primary">--accordion-button-padding</code></td>
                                <td>Default button padding.</td>
                            </tr>

                            <tr>
                                <td><code class="text-bold text-primary">--accordion-button-padding-lg</code></td>
                                <td>Padding for large buttons.</td>
                            </tr>

                            <tr>
                                <td><code class="text-bold text-primary">--accordion-button-padding-md</code></td>
                                <td>Padding for medium buttons.</td>
                            </tr>

                            <tr>
                                <td><code class="text-bold text-primary">--accordion-button-padding-sm</code></td>
                                <td>Padding for small buttons.</td>
                            </tr>

                            </tbody>
                        </table>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </article>

        </div>
